<paragraph id="8BB63706C347FFB7FFE7F9D1FBA5F966" blockId="11.[125,1172,1629,1685]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2066">This species can be distinguished by (1) broad connective; (2) broadly U-shaped aedeagus in lateral view; and (3) single pair of lateral aedeagal processes extending beyond shaft.</paragraph>
